                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="250210" author="adilger" created="Thu, 27 Jun 2019 22:37:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the same root cause as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12404&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test 69 fails with &amp;#39;create file after reformat&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12404&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12404&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, namely the patch from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11760&quot; title=&quot;formatted OST recognition change&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11760&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11760&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; allowing too many objects to be created, which is what &lt;tt&gt;test_69&lt;/tt&gt; is exactly trying to detect, but it was skipped because it is in the &lt;tt&gt;SLOW&lt;/tt&gt; group (about 10 minutes per test).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="248885" author="pfarrell" created="Mon, 10 Jun 2019 16:42:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While the test doesn&apos;t give enough output for me to be sure, I suspect the culprit is &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12396&quot; title=&quot;lfs df output is treated as binary data on RHEL 8.0 client&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12396&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12396&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(For a lot of ZFS failures)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
